Description: Includes Ibanez case, tremolo arm, and shown case candy. Here we have a used Ibanez JEM70VSFG in a beautiful sea foam green color. This is equipped with Dimarzio Evolution pickups, which sound absolutely massive in the American basswood body. It also features the original Edge bridge, which is known for amazing stability. The action on this is very low and free of buzz. The neck is straight, the fretwork is great, and everything on it functions as it should. This includes the original case, which isn't the most sturdy case I have ever seen. One of the latches doesn't seem to actually stay latched when the case is closed, and it seems like the original hinge screws were replaced by the previous owner. Condition: Overall, the guitar is in great condition, with the exception of two things: there is some chipping in the finish above the locking nut. There are also cracks at each side of the neck pocket. There is a small ding on the forearm contour. There are also light polish swirls and pick scratches from normal light use. Specs: -American basswood body- 5-piece Wizard Premium maple/walnut neck with KTS titanium reinforcement rods- Panga panga fretboard with Tree of Life Inlay- DiMarzio Evolution humbucker pickup (neck)- DiMarzio Evolution humbucker pickup (bridge)- DiMarzio Evolution single-coil pickup (middle)- 5-way pickup switching- Master volume and tone controls- Edge bridge and lion's claw cavity- Monkey Grip handle
Title: Ibanez JEM70V SFG Electric Guitar Vai Signature with Case Sea Foam Green Jem 70
